{% block content %}
<article class="fund-wrap fund-wrap--narrow">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">Council · About</p>
  <h1>About OIATC</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">The Ontario Indigenous AI and Technology Council exists because of a simple, repeated failure: the digital systems that run First Nations services are chosen by vendors and administrators, not by the communities they serve. We author governance for Indigenous-led digital decisions and we steward platforms that put that governance into use.</p>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>Where we are</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>OIATC is early and small on purpose. The council has three members: Russell Jones (Ojibwe from Sagamok Anishnawbek, founder, full-stack developer), Web Networks (a non-profit worker co-op, one of Canada's first ISPs, our hosting foundation), and Oliver Zielke (former Director at Web Networks, with a background in non-profit and open-source technology). Steven Bennett, a fluent speaker who shares his teachings of Anishinaabemowin, is our Elder and Knowledge Keeper. We are incorporating as a not-for-profit corporation; until that completes, partnership funds will be held under a trusteeship arrangement we name here. We publish what we ship, we date what we publish, and we correct what we get wrong.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>What we run</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>Four programs: <a href="/programs/anishinaabemowin">Anishinaabemowin</a> (language revitalization with consent infrastructure), <a href="/programs/anokii">Anokii</a> (community platforms designed to be Nation-governed), <a href="/programs/community-knowledge">Community Knowledge</a> (plain-language explainers for members), and <a href="/programs/member-resources">Transparency and Member Resources</a> (helping members see how their governments and systems work).</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>Who we're looking for</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>A Nation ready to be a first partner. A legal or policy advisor in Indigenous data governance. One more arm's-length director as we incorporate. And funders who want shipped work over slideware: everything on this site exists and is dated.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The council</h2>
    <div class="fund-profiles">
      <article class="fund-profile">
        <div class="fund-profile__k">Council member</div>
        <h3>Russell Jones</h3>
        <p class="fund-profile__meta">Ojibwe from Sagamok Anishnawbek · Founder · Full-stack developer</p>
        <p>In 2023 Russell was contracted to implement a case-management system at a First Nations Child and Family Advocacy Unit, saw within weeks that it would not fit the community, and made the case for a Canadian-built alternative already in use at neighbouring Nations. The recommendation was shelved and the contract ended. OIATC is how that lesson becomes a practice.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="fund-profile">
        <div class="fund-profile__k">Council member</div>
        <h3><a href="https://web.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Networks</a></h3>
        <p class="fund-profile__meta">Est. 1987 · One of Canada's first ISPs · Non-profit worker co-op · Canadian soil</p>
        <p>A non-profit worker co-op whose clients have included the Legislative Assembly of Nunavut and Nunavut Public Library Services. Web Networks provides OIATC's hosting foundation and sits on the council.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="fund-profile">
        <div class="fund-profile__k">Council member</div>
        <h3>Oliver Zielke</h3>
        <p class="fund-profile__meta">Director · Non-profit technology</p>
        <p>Former Director at Web Networks, with a background in non-profit and open-source technology. Joins the board as OIATC incorporates.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="fund-profiles fund-profiles--single">
      <article class="fund-profile">
        <div class="fund-profile__k">Elder · Knowledge Keeper</div>
        <h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61582894730998" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steven Bennett</a></h3>
        <p class="fund-profile__meta">Fluent speaker of Anishinaabemowin</p>
        <p>A fluent speaker who shares his teachings of Anishinaabemowin publicly. His recordings are the foundation of the language program, used with his agreement, and he guides the council on language and cultural knowledge.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>Council positions</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>Beyond the programs, OIATC publishes occasional council-level statements on national questions that bear on Indigenous digital sovereignty.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="fund-links">
      <li><span class="fund-tag">Council position</span> &nbsp; <a href="/positions/counter-disinformation">Foreign disinformation is a sovereignty issue</a></li>
      <li><span class="fund-tag">Council position</span> &nbsp; <a href="/positions/prescribeit">When the system is chosen for you: the PrescribeIT lesson</a></li>
      <li><span class="fund-tag">Council position</span> &nbsp; <a href="/positions/sovereign-ai">When a foreign order can switch off your AI, what do you actually own?</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>For partnerships, funding, or council questions, write to Russell: <a href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</a>. Writing to Russell is writing to OIATC.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</article>
